data.name: label1.Text
data.value: 1. Start the game by allocating your bet. 2. To win the game, you must reach 21 or the closest value to 21. 3. You can either Hit, which draws another card and adds to your total value, or Stand, which passes your turn. 4. If the Dealer reaches 21 or draws a closer value than you, the Dealer wins and your betted money is lost. 5. If both of you manage to draw the same value, a Draw occurs and your betted money is returned. 6. If your opening hand contains two cards of the same value, you can Split, which doubles your initial bet and redraws your hand while keeping your previous draw. 7. If the Dealer holds an ace, you can place an Insurance bet, which is half your current bet that you've placed. If you lose to the Dealer, your Insurance bet is retrieved and cashed out to you.
